.background
  section.section
    .notification.is-white.box(style='margin-top: 60px; margin-bottom: 60px;')
      #container.container.is-fluid
        .columns.is-centered
          #formdiv.column.is-two-fifths
            div
              form
                mat-stepper(orientation='vertical' #stepper='' [selectedindex]='7')
                  mat-step
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='')
                      div
                        | Select your area of interest on the map
                        span.has-tooltip-bottom.has-text-info(data-tooltip='For this area a satellite image will be created in order to subsequently perform a land use classification. \
                        To validate the result, the area of applicabilty (AOA) is also applied. The larger the selected area, the longer\
                        the calculation will take. For a faster calculation, the resolution and/or the number of bands could be reduced.\
                        Example: For an area of ​​approx. 10,000 hectares, a 10m resolution and all bands selected the software needs \
                        about 15 minutes to work.')
                          i.fa.fa-info-circle
                    div
                      p
                        | This is the area of interest selected for the demonstration.
                  mat-step(state='option')
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='')
                      div
                        | Do you have a trained model or just some training data?
                        span.has-tooltip-arrow.has-tooltip-bottom.has-text-info(data-tooltip='Choose whether you want to upload an trained model or training data to calculate a new model.\
                        When you select to upload training data, you will be able to choose between two machine learning algorithms.\
                        For each algorithm further hyperparameters can be set.\
                        • Random Forest:\
                        o mtry:\
                        - min: 2\
                        - max: Number of selected predictors (step 5)\
                        - default: 2\
                        • Support Vector Machine:\
                        o sigma:\
                        - default: 0.5\
                        o cost:\
                        - default: 1')
                          i.fa.fa-info-circle
                    .control
                      label.radio
                        input(type='radio' checked='' disabled='')
                        b Trained model
                      label.radio
                        input(type='radio' disabled='')
                        b Training data
                    .container
                      .field
                        button.button.has-background-info-light.is-pulled-right(mat-button='' matsteppernext='') Next
                  mat-step
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='')
                      div
                        | Select a file (trained model or training data)
                        span.has-tooltip-arrow.has-tooltip-bottom.has-text-info(data-tooltip='• Model:\
                        o If you choose to upload a model, please note, that all predictors used by the model must\
                        also be included in the selection of bands/predictors (step 5). The reverse need not apply.\
                        o To get reliable results, the uploaded model should also have been trained at the same resolution as selected in step 6.\
                        o Accepted formats:\
                        - .RDS\
                        • Training data:\
                        o Training data must be stored as polygons and contain a “Label” column.\
                        o Accepted formats:\
                        - .gpkg\
                        - .geojson')
                          i.fa.fa-info-circle
                    div
                      .file.has-name.is-boxed.is-centered
                        label.file-label
                          input.file-input(type='file' disabled='true')
                          span.file-cta
                            span.file-icon
                              i.fa.fa-upload
                          span.file-name(*ngif="this.currentFileName != ''")
                            | {{currentFileName}}
                      .container
                        .field
                          button.button.has-background-warning-light.is-pulled-left(mat-button='' matstepperprevious='') Back
                          button.button.has-background-info-light.is-pulled-right(mat-button='' matsteppernext='') Next
                  mat-step
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='')
                      div
                        | Choose bands/predictors (for outcome sentinel-2 images)
                        span.has-tooltip-arrow.has-tooltip-bottom.has-text-info(data-tooltip='The bands in our program are the possible predictors. The more predictors are selected, the more computational \
                        effort is required. Please choose your predictors carefully, depending on the goal of the calculations.')
                          i.fa.fa-info-circle
                    mat-form-field(appearance='fill')
                      mat-label Bands/predictors
                      mat-select(multiple='' [(ngmodel)]='selectedChannels' name='selectedFoods')
                        mat-option(value='B01' disabled='') B01
                        mat-option(value='B02' disabled='') B02
                        mat-option(value='B03' disabled='') B03
                        mat-option(value='B04' disabled='') B04
                        mat-option(value='B05' disabled='') B05
                        mat-option(value='B06' disabled='') B06
                        mat-option(value='B07' disabled='') B07
                        mat-option(value='B08' disabled='') B08
                        mat-option(value='B8A' disabled='') B8A
                        mat-option(value='B09' disabled='') B09
                        mat-option(value='B11' disabled='') B11
                        mat-option(value='B12' disabled='') B12
                    .container
                      .field
                        button.button.has-background-warning-light.is-pulled-left(mat-button='' matstepperprevious='') Back
                        button.button.has-background-info-light.is-pulled-right(mat-button='' matsteppernext='') Next
                  mat-step
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='')
                      div
                        | Choose the resolution (for outcome sentinel-2 images)
                        span.has-tooltip-arrow.has-tooltip-bottom.has-text-info(data-tooltip='Here the resolution of the satellite image for the area of interest (and if available also for the training data)\
                        is selected, on which all further calculations are based. The higher the resolution, the longer the runtime of\
                        the calculations. Please note, that some bands are only available up to a certain resolution (for further \
                        information: https://sentinels.copernicus.eu/web/sentinel/user-guides/sentinel-2-msi/resolutions/spatial).\
                        Depending on the desired resolution, the bands are up- or downsampled.')
                          i.fa.fa-info-circle
                    mat-form-field(appearance='fill')
                      mat-label Select an option
                      mat-select([(value)]='resolution')
                        mat-option(value='10' disabled='') 10m
                        mat-option(value='20' disabled='') 20m
                        mat-option(value='60' disabled='') 60m
                        mat-option(value='100' disabled='') 100m
                        mat-option(value='200' disabled='') 200m
                        mat-option(value='400' disabled='') 400m
                    .container
                      .field
                        button.button.has-background-warning-light.is-pulled-left(mat-button='' matstepperprevious='') Back
                        button.button.has-background-info-light.is-pulled-right(mat-button='' matsteppernext='') Next
                  mat-step
                    br
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='')
                      div
                        | Choose maximum cloud cover (for sentinel-2 image search)
                        span.has-tooltip-arrow.has-tooltip-bottom.has-text-info(data-tooltip='The cloud cover is used to retrieve available sentinel-2 imagery. The images found are processed to create the outcome sentinel images\
                        for the area of interest and for the training data (if uploaded). It is possible that suitable satellite images can be found for the \
                        selected time period, but not for the specified maximum cloud cover. If this is the case, a corresponding error message will be displayed \
                        and you will be prompted to increase the maximum cloud cover. Please note that increasing the maximum cloud cover will probably produce\
                        worse sentinel images (more gaps, clouds or other artifacts). If you want to keep the same maximum cloud cover, you can instead increase the\
                        selected time period.')
                          i.fa.fa-info-circle
                    .columns.is-mobile.is-centered
                      .column.is-half
                        p.bd-notification.is-primary
                          mat-slider(thumblabel='' tickinterval='1' step='1' min='0' max='100' aria-label='units' value='20' disabled='')
                    .container
                      .field
                        button.button.has-background-warning-light.is-pulled-left(mat-button='' matstepperprevious='') Back
                        button.button.has-background-info-light.is-pulled-right(mat-button='' matsteppernext='') Next
                  mat-step
                    ng-template(matsteplabel='') Done
                    
